<p>Ready to try it? Refresh! There's our weird-little summary. We can use this
across our app, and if we ever want to change how it looks, we only need
to update one spot.</p>
<h3 id="method-arguments">Method Arguments <a class="headerlink" href="methods-work#method-arguments" title="Permalink to this headline"><i class="fa fa-link" aria-hidden="true"></i></a></h3>
<p>Being PHP pro's, we of course know that functions can have arguments. Once
again, a method in a class is no different. Isn't that nice? Let's say that
sometimes we need an even <em>shorter</em> summary. Add an argument to the method
called <code>$useShortFormat</code>. Now, use an <code>if</code> statement to choose between two
different formats:</p>
